The Chinese Canadian Association of Kingston and District was founded in **1974** by a small group of Chinese Canadians who wanted to create a welcoming community for families in the Kingston area.

Over the past five decades, CCAKD has grown from a handful of founding members to a vibrant organization serving hundreds of families. We have organized countless cultural events, educational programs, and community gatherings that bring people together.

Key milestones include our annual Chinese New Year celebrations, the establishment of our community programs, and ongoing partnerships with local organizations to promote multicultural understanding in Kingston.
